data.title: Waimea Town Celebration
data.text:
KAUA'I COCKTAILS & CUISINE @ the Historic Waimea Theater

Spend the evening immersed in our opening night's event HOT HAVANA NIGHTS! Come dressed the part and enter our costume contest for CASH prize.

$60* General Admission / $80* VIP 6:00 pm entry (*Must be 21+ to enter.)

KING KAUMUALI'I LU'AU @ the Historic Waimea Theater

A cultural presentation of beautiful songs and dance by Kumu Hula Troy Lazaro & Halau Ka Pa Hula o Hinano in honor of Kaua'i's favorite King Kaumuali'i. Doors open at 4:30 pm.

$40 General Admission includes a special meal. Get Tickets Here:

WAIMEA FILM FESTIVAL - HIFF HANA HOU @ the Historic Waimea Theater

Asian Pacific films including an encore of award-winning films & sleepers from the Hawaii International Film Festival 44. Trailers and film summaries on www.WaimeaTheater.com.

$10 tickets sold at the Box Office and $30 All Day Pass includes special meal (served at 12:30 pm) and can be purchased online.

KAUA'I PANIOLO SHOWDOWN 2023 @ Friendship Do's Ranch, Waimea Arena

Come and see Hawai'i's best battle it out. All events are open to the public.

$10 Admission Fee only on Saturday for persons 2 years and older

Thu 7:00 pm - World's Best Muley Roping

Fri 8:30 am - Team Roping Qualifying Slack

Fri 7:00 pm - Barrel Racing Qualifying Slack

Sat 10:00 am - Po'o Waiu, Roping, Barrels, Double Mugging & MORE

Na Heihei a Ola 2K, 5K & 10K Fun Run @ Waimea Plantation Cottages

This Fun Run attracts a mixed field of keiki to kupuna. Cost is $50/Adults, $30/Juniors (17 years and younger). Register online or on Friday night at the Ho'olaule'a (in front of the Beer Garden) from 4:30 pm to 10:00 pm.
